result.execSummary:
The defendant Sarah J Hraban was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Reserve Judge Robert Mawdsley presiding for Branch IV
Defendant Sarah J Hraban in court with Attorney Sandra J. Zenor.   ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights given; plea of " No Contest " entered on Count #2 of Case 15CM292 and Count #1 of Case 15CM354; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court reads in and dismisses all remaining counts of both cases
Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Ms. Hraban

As to Case 15CM292, Count #2:
The Court sentences the Defendant to pay a fine of $100+ costs = $379 plus $200 DNA surcharge plus $17 drug testing fee  

As to Case 15CM354, Count #1: 
The Court sentences the Defendant to pay a fine of $100+ costs = $473.50 plus $200 DNA surcharge plus $25 drug testing fee

The total of both cases, $1294.50 is to be paid in $25 per month installments commencing on 12/15/15 and on the 15th day of each month thereafter until paid in full. Non-payment shall result in a 25 day jail term, with Huber privileges consecutive.
